!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

flood /flʌd/

(flooding,flooded,floods) 

1. N-VAR If there is a flood , a large amount of water covers an area which is usually dry, for example, when a river flows over its banks or a pipe bursts. 洪水 

例： More than 70 people were killed in the floods, caused when a dam burst. 大坝决堤引发的洪水灾吞噬了七十多人的生命。 

例： This is the type of flood dreaded by cavers. 这正是探察洞穴者惧怕的那种洪水。 

2. V-T/V-I If something such as a river or a burst pipe floods an area that is usually dry or if the area floods , it becomes covered with water. 为水所淹; 淹没 

例： The kitchen flooded. 厨房被水淹了。 

3. V-I If a river floods , it overflows, especially after very heavy rain. 泛滥 

例： ...the relentless rain that caused twenty rivers to flood. …导致20条河流泛滥的那场持续不断的雨。 

4. V-I If you say that people or things flood into a place, you are emphasizing that they arrive there in large numbers. 涌入 [强调] 

例： Large numbers of immigrants flooded into the area. 大批移民涌入了这个地区。 

例： Inquiries flooded in from all over the world. 问询从世界各地如潮水般涌来。 

5. V-T If you flood a place with a particular type of thing, or if a particular type of thing floods a place, the place becomes full of so many of them that it cannot hold or deal with any more. 使充满; 充斥 

例： Manufacturers are destroying American jobs by flooding the market with cheap imports. 制造商们在以廉价进口货充斥市场，破坏了美国人的就业机会。 

6. N-COUNT If you say that a flood of people or things arrive somewhere, you are emphasizing that a very large number of them arrive there. 一大批 [强调] 

例： The administration is trying to stem the flood of refugees out of Haiti and into Florida. 政府正设法阻止大批逃离海地的难民涌入佛罗里达。

</div>

